        "description": "POST /hgs/rest/collectors/records/amazon/connect\n\nPurpose:\nThis request registers an Amazon (AWS) account with the Hyperglance collector service. It sends AWS credentials and configuration so the platform can validate access and create a collector record.\n\nEnvironment & variables required:\n- local: base URL for local API (e.g. http://localhost:8080)\n- access_key: AWS access key ID\n- secret_key: AWS secret access key\n- uniqueAlias: autogenerated alias for this record (pre-request script sets it)\n\nRequest details:\n- Method: POST\n- URL: {{local}}/hgs/rest/collectors/records/amazon/connect\n- Content-Type: application/json\n- Body (raw JSON):\n  {\n    \"alias\": \"{{uniqueAlias}}\",\n    \"accessKey\": \"{{access_key}}\",\n    \"secretKey\": \"{{secret_key}}\",\n    \"assumedRoleARN\": \"\",\n    \"awsOrganization\": false,\n    \"regions\": [\"us-east-1\", \"us-west-2\"],\n    \"billingOnly\": false,\n    \"organizationalUnitID\": \"ou-xxxx-xxxxxxxx\"\n  }\n\nNotes on fields:\n- alias: a unique human-readable name for the record. The pre-request script populates uniqueAlias automatically.\n- accessKey/secretKey: credentials to validate AWS API access. Keep these in environment or vault variables, not in request body literals.\n- assumedRoleARN: optional, when using STS-assumed roles.\n- awsOrganization: set true if you want organization-wide collection.\n- regions: list of regions to validate/collect from.\n- billingOnly: if true, only billing data will be collected.\n- organizationalUnitID: optional AWS OU ID when awsOrganization=true.\n\nSuccessful response example (200):\n{\n  \"id\": 67,\n  \"status\": {\n    \"isSuccess\": true,\n    \"datasource\": \"Amazon\",\n    \"recordAlias\": \"MyAWSAccount-1762334825988-81798\",\n    \"status\": \"VALID\",\n    \"warnings\": []\n  }\n}\n\nTests included in this request (post-response script):\n- Status code is 200\n- Response body contains status.isSuccess === true\n- datasource is 'Amazon'\n- recordAlias matches alias sent in request\n\nSecurity reminder:\n- Do not commit real AWS credentials into source control. Use Postman environment variables or vault secrets and limit access.\n\nTroubleshooting:\n- 400: malformed JSON or invalid field values (see nearby example requests in this collection for invalid payloads)\n- 401/403: invalid credentials or insufficient permissions\n\nReferences: see other requests in this collection that demonstrate invalid payloads and edge cases (InvalidJSON, InvalidRegion, InvalidDataType, ExtraField, UnknownFields)."
